fields.description:
It is difficult for human beings to work on or under water for a long time. Our vision is to replace them by an unmanned marine robot which can be controlled from a safe location i.e. Ocean Mate. We will be targeting oil platforms (rigs) where people go underwater for maintenance purpose, and also to  to carry out security operations (like monitoring, spying etc).

Interested people are invited to join. Contact us at 136390003@iitb.ac.in, 136330004@iitb.ac.in

fields.purpose: To take part in a project
To learn basic stuff for tech events.
To get access to components and improve technical skills

Currently need to fix my watchstrap after making the necessary bits. I have the aluminum strip needed. I need to use the following tools: a vice, hacksaw, file, 1mm drillbit & drilling machine (hand-drill is OK) OR a sharp straight hard rod with 1mm with pointed tip to make the holes.

In due course, I'd like to explore making a hand-cranked charger for my cellphone & my tab. And subsequently, a battery bank for my tab.
